<p>I know how to check if no records were created in one model.</p>  <pre><code>expect{Counter.increment}.to_not change{Counter.count}.by(1) </code></pre>  <p><a href="https://www.relishapp.com/rspec/rspec-expectations/v/2-2/docs/matchers/expect-change#expecting-no-change" rel="nofollow">https://www.relishapp.com/rspec/rspec-expectations/v/2-2/docs/matchers/expect-change#expecting-no-change</a></p>  <p>Now, is there a way to check if no records were created among all models in RSpec/Rails?</p>